15#ifndef OPENSSL_HEADER_X509_INTERNAL_H
16#define OPENSSL_HEADER_X509_INTERNAL_H
17
18#include <openssl/base.h>
19#include <openssl/evp.h>
20#include <openssl/x509.h>
21
22#if defined(__cplusplus)
23extern "C" {
24#endif
25
26
27/* Internal structures. */
28
29struct X509_val_st {
30 ASN1_TIME *notBefore;
31 ASN1_TIME *notAfter;
32} /* X509_VAL */;
33
34struct X509_pubkey_st {
35 X509_ALGOR *algor;
36 ASN1_BIT_STRING *public_key;
37 EVP_PKEY *pkey;
38} /* X509_PUBKEY */;
39
40struct x509_attributes_st {
41 ASN1_OBJECT *object;
42 STACK_OF(ASN1_TYPE) *set;
43} /* X509_ATTRIBUTE */;
44
45struct x509_cert_aux_st {
46 STACK_OF(ASN1_OBJECT) *trust; // trusted uses
47 STACK_OF(ASN1_OBJECT) *reject; // rejected uses
48 ASN1_UTF8STRING *alias; // "friendly name"
49 ASN1_OCTET_STRING *keyid; // key id of private key
50 STACK_OF(X509_ALGOR) *other; // other unspecified info
51} /* X509_CERT_AUX */;
52
53
54/* RSA-PSS functions. */
55
56/* x509_rsa_pss_to_ctx configures |ctx| for an RSA-PSS operation based on
57 * signature algorithm parameters in |sigalg| (which must have type
58 * |NID_rsassaPss|) and key |pkey|. It returns one on success and zero on
59 * error. */
60int x509_rsa_pss_to_ctx(EVP_MD_CTX *ctx, X509_ALGOR *sigalg, EVP_PKEY *pkey);
61
62/* x509_rsa_pss_to_ctx sets |algor| to the signature algorithm parameters for
63 * |ctx|, which must have been configured for an RSA-PSS signing operation. It
64 * returns one on success and zero on error. */
65int x509_rsa_ctx_to_pss(EVP_MD_CTX *ctx, X509_ALGOR *algor);
66
67/* x509_print_rsa_pss_params prints a human-readable representation of RSA-PSS
68 * parameters in |sigalg| to |bp|. It returns one on success and zero on
69 * error. */
70int x509_print_rsa_pss_params(BIO *bp, const X509_ALGOR *sigalg, int indent,
71 ASN1_PCTX *pctx);
72
73
74/* Signature algorithm functions. */
75
76/* x509_digest_sign_algorithm encodes the signing parameters of |ctx| as an
77 * AlgorithmIdentifer and saves the result in |algor|. It returns one on
78 * success, or zero on error. */
79int x509_digest_sign_algorithm(EVP_MD_CTX *ctx, X509_ALGOR *algor);
80
81/* x509_digest_verify_init sets up |ctx| for a signature verification operation
82 * with public key |pkey| and parameters from |algor|. The |ctx| argument must
83 * have been initialised with |EVP_MD_CTX_init|. It returns one on success, or
84 * zero on error. */
85int x509_digest_verify_init(EVP_MD_CTX *ctx, X509_ALGOR *sigalg,
86 EVP_PKEY *pkey);
87
88
89#if defined(__cplusplus)
90} /* extern C */
91#endif
92
93#endif /* OPENSSL_HEADER_X509_INTERNAL_H */
